What is 6G and what its gonna be
•	6G huge shift from 5G.
•	Need 1 Tbps speeds and millions of IoT devices per km2.
•	Ground and satellite systems together for global coverage.
•	Move to O-RAN architecture.
•	Old way was locked hardware/software from one vendor.
•	O-RAN splits hardware and software so different vendors work together.
•	AI runs the network using controllers.
•	xApps for fast tasks and rApps for long tasks.
•	Apps automate resource stuff and signal beam routing.

Networks no longer behind wall
•	Open design is flexible but has bad security.
•	Old security used castle and moat where inside was safe.
•	6G has virtual cloud and too many devices so no physical boundary.
•	Attackers use weak IoT to get in and move around.


